### DSP4D - LLM API Testing
### Test both Ollama and OpenAI-compatible endpoints
### Click the green "Run" arrow next to each request to execute it

### Variables
@customEndpoint = https://ai.bniweb.ch
@apiKey = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpZCI6ImY0MzgwNzRlLTg1MTUtNDcyOC1iZDg2LWJjMDQ2MmY4ZTcwYiIsImV4cCI6MTc2NTk4MjM4Nn0.vJQ4BLvJJ84qOSDjy0G5Wsdr22Xyu2hAyMkSFb7AU0c
@model = gemma3:27b
@contentType = application/json

### =============================================================================
### Diagnostic Tests - Find Available Endpoints
### =============================================================================

### 0a. Test Root Path
GET {{customEndpoint}}/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

### 0b. Test API Info (common endpoint)
GET {{customEndpoint}}/api
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

### 0c. Test Health/Status
GET {{customEndpoint}}/health
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

### 0d. Test Version Info
GET {{customEndpoint}}/version
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

### 0e. Try without trailing slash
GET {{customEndpoint}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

### 0f. Test chat/completions without /v1 prefix
POST {{customEndpoint}}/chat/completions
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "model": "{{model}}",
  "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}]
}

### 0g. Test completions endpoint
POST {{customEndpoint}}/completions
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "model": "{{model}}",
  "prompt": "Hello"
}

### 0h. Test with x-api-key header instead
POST {{customEndpoint}}/api/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "model": "{{model}}",
  "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}]
}

### 0i. Test with Authorization without Bearer
POST {{customEndpoint}}/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "model": "{{model}}",
  "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}]
}

### 0j. Check if it's a web UI - look for API docs path
GET {{customEndpoint}}/docs
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

### 0k. Check for API documentation
GET {{customEndpoint}}/api-docs
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

### =============================================================================
### OpenAI-Compatible API Tests (Custom Endpoint)
### =============================================================================

### 1. Test OpenAI API - Chat Completions
POST {{customEndpoint}}/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "model": "{{model}}",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a medical document summarization assistant."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Summarize this medical document: Patient presents with acute chest pain radiating to left arm. ECG shows ST elevation in leads II, III, aVF. Troponin levels elevated at 2.5 ng/mL. Immediate cardiology consultation recommended."
    }
  ],
  "temperature": 0.7,
  "max_tokens": 500
}

### 2. Test OpenAI API - Simple Prompt
POST {{customEndpoint}}/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "model": "{{model}}",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the capital of Switzerland?"
    }
  ]
}

### =============================================================================
### Ollama API Tests (Local or Custom Ollama Endpoint)
### =============================================================================

### 3. Test Ollama API - Generate
POST {{customEndpoint}}/api/generate
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "model": "{{model}}",
  "prompt": "Summarize this medical document: Patient presents with acute chest pain radiating to left arm. ECG shows ST elevation in leads II, III, aVF. Troponin levels elevated at 2.5 ng/mL.",
  "stream": false
}

### 4. Test Ollama API - Chat
POST {{customEndpoint}}/api/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "model": "{{model}}",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a medical assistant."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What are the symptoms of a heart attack?"
    }
  ],
  "stream": false
}

### =============================================================================
### Model Information Tests
### =============================================================================

### 5. List Available Models (OpenAI format)
GET {{customEndpoint}}/v1/models
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

### 6. List Available Models (Ollama format)
GET {{customEndpoint}}/api/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

### 2. Summarize Medical Document - Lab Results
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/documents/summarize
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "content": "Complete Blood Count Results:\n\nWBC: 12.5 x10^9/L (Normal: 4-11)\nRBC: 4.2 x10^12/L (Normal: 4.5-5.5)\nHemoglobin: 13.8 g/dL (Normal: 13-17)\nPlatelets: 250 x10^9/L (Normal: 150-400)\n\nChemistry Panel:\nGlucose: 145 mg/dL (slightly elevated)\nCreatinine: 1.1 mg/dL (Normal)\nAST: 28 U/L (Normal)\nALT: 32 U/L (Normal)\n\nNote: Mild leukocytosis present. Patient reports recent upper respiratory infection."
}

### 3. Summarize Medical Document - Consultation Note
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/documents/summarize
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "content": "Cardiology Consultation\n\nPatient: 62-year-old male\nChief Complaint: Exertional dyspnea and fatigue for 3 months\n\nHistory of Present Illness:\nPatient reports progressive shortness of breath with minimal exertion over the past 3 months. Associated symptoms include orthopnea (2-pillow), paroxysmal nocturnal dyspnea, and bilateral lower extremity edema.\n\nPhysical Examination:\n- BP: 145/90 mmHg\n- HR: 92 bpm, irregular\n- Lungs: Bilateral basilar crackles\n- Heart: S3 gallop present, irregular rhythm\n- Extremities: 2+ bilateral pitting edema\n\nAssessment:\nCongestive heart failure, likely due to atrial fibrillation with rapid ventricular response.\n\nPlan:\n1. Initiate diuretic therapy (Furosemide 40mg daily)\n2. Rate control with beta-blocker\n3. Echocardiogram scheduled\n4. Consider anticoagulation after risk stratification\n5. Follow-up in 2 weeks"
}

### =============================================================================
### Document Classification Endpoints
### =============================================================================

### 4. Classify Document - Lab Results
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/documents/classify
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "content": "Lab Results - Complete Blood Count: WBC 12.5, RBC 4.2, Hemoglobin 13.8 g/dL, Platelets 250k. All values within normal range except mild leukocytosis."
}

### 5. Classify Document - Emergency
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/documents/classify
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "content": "STAT - Patient with severe chest pain, ST elevation on ECG, troponin 5.2 ng/mL. IMMEDIATE INTERVENTION REQUIRED. Activating cath lab."
}

### 6. Classify Document - Routine Follow-up
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/documents/classify
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "content": "Routine follow-up visit. Patient doing well on current medications. Blood pressure controlled at 130/80. No new complaints. Continue current regimen. Next appointment in 6 months."
}

### 7. Classify Document - Radiology Report
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/documents/classify
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "content": "Chest X-Ray Report: PA and lateral views obtained. Lungs are clear bilaterally. No infiltrates, effusions, or pneumothorax. Cardiac silhouette normal size. Impression: Normal chest radiograph."
}

### =============================================================================
### Entity Extraction Endpoints
### =============================================================================

### 8. Extract Entities - Full Medical Note
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/documents/extract-entities
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "content": "Patient: 55-year-old male with Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus\n\nMedications:\n- Metformin 1000mg BID\n- Lisinopril 10mg daily\n- Atorvastatin 20mg at bedtime\n- Aspirin 81mg daily\n\nVitals:\n- BP: 135/82 mmHg\n- HR: 76 bpm\n- Temp: 36.8°C\n- SpO2: 98% on room air\n\nLab Results:\n- HbA1c: 7.2% (target <7%)\n- LDL: 95 mg/dL\n- Creatinine: 1.0 mg/dL\n- eGFR: 88 mL/min\n\nAssessment:\n1. Type 2 Diabetes - fair control\n2. Hypertension - well controlled\n3. Hyperlipidemia - at goal\n\nPlan:\n- Continue current medications\n- Dietary counseling\n- Increase physical activity\n- Recheck HbA1c in 3 months"
}

### 9. Extract Entities - Prescription Note
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/documents/extract-entities
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "content": "New Prescriptions:\n\n1. Amoxicillin 500mg - Take 1 capsule by mouth three times daily for 10 days\n2. Ibuprofen 400mg - Take 1 tablet by mouth every 6 hours as needed for pain\n3. Omeprazole 20mg - Take 1 capsule by mouth once daily before breakfast\n\nDiagnoses:\n- Acute bacterial sinusitis\n- GERD (Gastroesophageal reflux disease)\n\nFollow-up if symptoms persist after 7 days."
}

### 10. Extract Entities - Procedure Note
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/documents/extract-entities
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "content": "Procedure: Colonoscopy with polypectomy\n\nIndication: Screening, positive FIT test\n\nProcedure Details:\n- Cecum reached at 12 minutes\n- Two polyps identified in sigmoid colon (6mm and 8mm)\n- Both polyps removed via snare polypectomy\n- Specimens sent to pathology\n\nFindings:\n- 6mm sessile polyp at 25cm (removed)\n- 8mm pedunculated polyp at 30cm (removed)\n- Otherwise normal mucosa throughout colon\n\nPathology pending.\n\nRecommendation: Follow-up colonoscopy in 3 years based on pathology results."
}

